{
  "texts": [
    "Human attention tends to wander when they are not actively engaged in a task.",
    "When systems operate as expected, humans become complacent.",
    "The difficulty of sustaining attention for monitoring purposes over longer periods of time is also known as vigilance decrement (Martínez-Pérez et al., 2023).",
    "What is egregious about allowing accountability to fall on only an inattentive human operator is that organizations should know better.",
    "Attention wandering was first noted in British naval radar operators who increasingly missed critical radar signals (enemy combatants) as their watch periods progressed."
  ]
}